- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper mentions the development of a language parser based on category grammars. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as Lambek Calculus is a formal grammar system used in natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the ability to support context-sensitive languages through customized extensions, which could be relevant to machine learning applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with a formalization of a logical system, which could be relevant to AI applications.
